1
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:12,233
<i> I understand you, Bobby.</i>

2
00:00:12,367 --> 00:00:13,533
<i> So even though it's hard,</i>

3
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:16,500
<i>I'll just accept your decision
to reject me.</i>

4
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:18,500
<i>What's with you, Tonyo?
That's not it!</i>

5
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:21,700
<i>I'm just saying,
let's take it slow.</i>

6
00:00:21,833 --> 00:00:24,000
<i>I want to fall in love
the right way.</i>

7
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,500
<i> I want to be sure with us.</i>

8
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:30,533
<i>I thought I could help Monty
because I love him.</i>

9
00:00:30,667 --> 00:00:31,667
<i> If he loved you,</i>

10
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,533
<i>he wouldn't let you
get in trouble like this.</i>

11
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,833
<i> Monty ruined your future.</i>

12
00:00:35,967 --> 00:00:38,167
<i>So you, don't be blinded
by love.</i>

13
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:40,167
<i>Use your brain,
not just your heart.</i>

14
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:42,133
<i>I'll be transferred
to Calabari State Prison.</i>

15
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:44,667
<i>If I don't leave this place,
I'll start talking.</i>

16
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:46,567
<i>Are you sure Bobby is the one
you're talking to?</i>

17
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:47,600
<i>- Let me see?
- What?</i>

18
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:49,800
<i> Just kidding, Dad.</i>

19
00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:51,567
<i>I know you're telling the truth</i>

20
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:53,300
<i>unless you're hiding something
from me.</i>

21
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:55,867
<i>We all hide something,
right, Son?</i>

22
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,867
<i> I'd like to ask for your help.</i>

23
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,333
<i>That's Jun Alferez,
he's missing.</i>

24
00:01:00,467 --> 00:01:02,100
<i> Does he have enemies?</i>

25
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:04,067
<i>What was his purpose
before he disappeared?</i>

26
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,700
Nothing, I don't remember
anything.

27
00:01:08,867 --> 00:01:09,967
Okay, Mayor.

28
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:13,033
When I hear anything,
I'll call you right away.

29
00:01:14,233 --> 00:01:16,167
I'll also get help
at the police station, Mayor.

30
00:01:17,467 --> 00:01:19,533
Do you still call me mayor?

31
00:01:21,867 --> 00:01:24,100
You still can't call me father?

32
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:27,700
Never mind,

33
00:01:28,467 --> 00:01:30,500
I can wait.

34
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:35,467
And when that day comes,
I'm sure I'll be very happy.

35
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:40,200
Copy.

36
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:43,967
Mayor, someone wants
to talk to you.

37
00:01:44,233 --> 00:01:45,267
They're very insistent.

38
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:48,200
Let them in.

39
00:01:58,267 --> 00:02:00,133
What can I do for you?

40
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:03,800
Mayor, why has the killer
of our sister,

41
00:02:03,933 --> 00:02:07,567
Anika Santos,
not been caught yet?

42
00:02:07,933 --> 00:02:09,500
She was your daughter's
classmate.

43
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:14,700
I'm sorry about what happened
to your sister,

44
00:02:14,867 --> 00:02:17,867
but I know that the case is
already in the police's hands.

45
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,100
Maybe you're covering
something up, Mayor,

46
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,767
and you're the one who started
the crime here.

47
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,333
Wait a minute. Why are you
yelling at the mayor?

48
00:02:23,467 --> 00:02:25,567
Who are you?
Why are you interfering in this?

49
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,167
Wait a minute,
wait a minute.

50
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,567
I know something bad happened
to your sister,

51
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:32,333
and I offer my condolences.

52
00:02:32,467 --> 00:02:37,933
But if you hurt my daughter
again, we'll have problems.

53
00:03:09,733 --> 00:03:13,300
We sympathize with what
happened to your sister,

54
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:17,100
and I promise you
that I will help you

55
00:03:17,233 --> 00:03:21,200
as much as I can to solve
this case.

56
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:28,500
All I ask is that you trust us
and the Calabari police.

57
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:32,133
Do we understand each other?

58
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:35,667
Okay, Mayor.

59
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,000
I'm sorry.

60
00:03:38,967 --> 00:03:40,733
- Okay.
- We're going home.

61
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:49,133
I'm sorry about that, Bobby.

62
00:03:49,267 --> 00:03:51,600
By the way, I'll go ahead.

63
00:03:51,733 --> 00:03:53,833
I still have to call the Major.

64
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,567
Okay.

65
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:05,067
Hey Dude, finish what Kapitana
asked you to do right away.

66
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:07,133
Mar, come on.

67
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:08,900
Bobby called.

68
00:04:09,033 --> 00:04:09,800
What did she say?

69
00:04:09,933 --> 00:04:12,667
We're invited
to the Mayor's birthday.

70
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:13,900
Then do you know
what the theme is?

71
00:04:14,033 --> 00:04:14,900
What?

72
00:04:15,033 --> 00:04:17,700
Hawaiian, not pizza.

73
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:18,867
- Hawaiian?
- Right?

74
00:04:20,167 --> 00:04:22,467
I'll borrow a grass skirt
from Mamu

75
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,633
and then a clamshell bra!

76
00:04:24,767 --> 00:04:25,800
I love it!

77
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:28,100
Friend, Moana is our peg.

78
00:04:28,267 --> 00:04:29,667
- Right?
- I like that. Right?

79
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,567
Hey, hey, hey.

80
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:35,667
Moana is not a hairy guy!
You should be ashamed!

81
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:38,133
Kapitana, you're killing
the vibe.

82
00:04:38,267 --> 00:04:40,100
Kapitana, this is our chance
to look good.

83
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:41,733
Don't try to stop us.
Oh my god!

84
00:04:41,867 --> 00:04:43,467
Where's the beauty?

85
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:47,600
Kapitana, you're not
our target market!

86
00:04:47,733 --> 00:04:52,133
As for me, I'll show
the Vice Mayor my hula dance!

87
00:04:52,267 --> 00:04:53,433
Like this, oh.

88
00:04:53,567 --> 00:04:54,867
Friend, that's ugly.

89
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,533
He'll just ignore you.

90
00:04:56,667 --> 00:04:59,300
And my waist is tighter
than yours.

91
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:01,900
I'll elbow you
with my cruel hips.

92
00:05:02,067 --> 00:05:02,967
Am I right?

93
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:04,867
You know, the Vice Mayor
will never notice you.

94
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,700
- I told you so.
-Because you look like a carpet.

95
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:09,800
Then he should step on me.

96
00:05:11,433 --> 00:05:12,367
Oh, my!

97
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:14,833
Why are you so obsessed
with the Vice Mayor?

98
00:05:14,967 --> 00:05:16,067
He's not my type!

99
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:18,667
Oh, really, Kapitana?

100
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:22,233
He's the reason you were rescued
from the kidnappers, isn't he?

101
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:24,500
That's right, Kapitana!
You're ungrateful!

102
00:05:24,633 --> 00:05:26,267
You should feel guilty!

103
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:29,767
Yes, I know, he saved me.

104
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:31,700
Well, I see that as a debt
of gratitude.

105
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:32,700
That's okay.

106
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:35,333
But I really don't like him

107
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:37,700
because I feel something off
about him.

108
00:05:37,833 --> 00:05:39,600
There's something.

109
00:05:39,733 --> 00:05:40,667
What's that?

110
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:44,433
That Vice Mayor seems fake.

111
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:46,367
Oh my...

112
00:05:48,133 --> 00:05:48,900
Boss...

113
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:51,900
Relax, everything's okay.

114
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,833
Why? Is the Mayor still
suspicious of you?

115
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:56,867
I don't know.

116
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:01,667
I'll just let his doubts slide,
after all,

117
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:04,600
he doesn't know anything
about me yet.

118
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,600
His man has also fallen silent.

119
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:15,633
What if he'll have you follow
you again?

120
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,867
And he'll find out something
about you.

121
00:06:20,533 --> 00:06:22,633
I'll answer that
when it happens.

122
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:24,833
He's still my father.

123
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:27,867
Worst comes to worst,

124
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,300
I hope he remembers
that I'm still his son.

125
00:06:34,933 --> 00:06:35,700
Boss...

126
00:06:36,467 --> 00:06:37,633
Monty called.

127
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,933
What did he say?

128
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:43,800
If we don't let him escape,
he'll expose and implicate you.

129
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:48,033
That animal is so brave.

130
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,367
What's your plan, Boss?

131
00:06:57,967 --> 00:07:02,133
Patrol the plaza,
and the informal settlers area.

132
00:07:02,267 --> 00:07:03,400
I'm not happy anymore.

133
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:05,400
That Mateo Ramos
hasn't been caught yet.

134
00:07:05,533 --> 00:07:06,433
Sir.

135
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:09,833
- Go ahead!
- Copy, Major.

136
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,367
Hello?

137
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:25,500
Espina is about to leave.

138
00:07:26,267 --> 00:07:28,033
There are two lieutenant escorts
with him.

139
00:07:40,367 --> 00:07:43,033
Hey, what are you doing there?

140
00:07:43,167 --> 00:07:44,667
It's embarrassing, Bobby.
We're not prepared.

141
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:45,667
Yes.

142
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,833
- Come on, that's okay!
- That's okay.

143
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,667
- Is that right?
- That's right.

144
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,200
- Is that right?
- Hey, it's embarrassing.

145
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:52,633
We're not prepared.

146
00:07:52,767 --> 00:07:56,300
- It's embarassing.
- Really? You weren't prepared?

147
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:57,333
Hey!

148
00:07:57,467 --> 00:08:01,100
- Best in costume.
- You two, both of you...

149
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:03,367
- Mayor.
- Bobby, thank you very much

150
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,400
for coming.

151
00:08:04,533 --> 00:08:08,400
- Happy birthday, Mayor!
- Thank you!

152
00:08:08,533 --> 00:08:09,300
Wait a minute...

153
00:08:09,433 --> 00:08:10,700
It looks like
you weren't prepared.

154
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:13,933
- No, we weren't. Yes.
- This is normal. Yes, yes.

155
00:08:14,067 --> 00:08:15,833
By the way,
where is your grandmother?

156
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:19,067
She won't be able to make it.
She's busy in the village.

157
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,867
Is that so?

158
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:21,867
Oh, come on.

159
00:08:23,267 --> 00:08:24,467
Why don't you eat there, huh?

160
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,500
Go ahead, eat.

161
00:08:25,633 --> 00:08:28,167
- Can we have takeout?
- Sharon.

162
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,633
- What? Takeout?
- Yes.

163
00:08:29,767 --> 00:08:32,133
Go ahead,
do whatever you want.

164
00:08:32,267 --> 00:08:34,533
Just eat. Go ahead, eat!

165
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:36,633
- Stop it.
- Go ahead!

166
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:39,167
Excuse those two.

167
00:08:39,300 --> 00:08:42,300
- Come on.
- That's how they are.

168
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:43,567
Oh, my.

169
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:44,767
Come on, come here.

170
00:08:47,433 --> 00:08:49,767
- Thank you.
- That's it.

171
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:50,900
Yes.

172
00:08:53,733 --> 00:08:54,933
Mayor, I have a present for you.

173
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:56,100
- Happy birthday.
- Oh my, you even went out

174
00:08:56,233 --> 00:08:58,100
of your way. Thank you so much!

175
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:03,833
Let me take a look.
Oh my, this is so beautiful.

176
00:09:04,867 --> 00:09:07,567
Bobby, I'll wear this, okay?
Just stay there.

177
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:11,200
Mayor, it doesn't fit
your birthday motif.

178
00:09:11,333 --> 00:09:13,267
That shirt is perfect
for the office.

179
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,900
Bobby, I don't care
about the motifs.

180
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:18,433
As long as I want to wear it,
I'll wear it.

181
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:21,767
This is your first gift to me.

182
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,700
Wait a minute,
I'll wear it first.

183
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:25,867
Oh, this suits me.

184
00:09:30,867 --> 00:09:32,800
<i> I'm sorry for your loss,</i>

185
00:09:32,933 --> 00:09:35,433
<i>but if you hurt
my daughter again,</i>

186
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:38,433
<i> we'll have problems.</i>

187
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:40,733
<i> Do you still call me Mayor?</i>

188
00:09:40,867 --> 00:09:43,567
<i> You still can't call me dad?</i>

189
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:46,833
<i> Never mind, I can wait.</i>

190
00:09:46,967 --> 00:09:51,633
<i>And when that day comes,
I'm sure I'll be very happy.</i>

191
00:09:57,133 --> 00:09:58,067
What?

192
00:09:58,367 --> 00:09:59,900
Doesn't it suit me?

193
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:01,200
I told you.

194
00:10:02,467 --> 00:10:04,533
Thank you very much.

195
00:10:04,667 --> 00:10:06,633
Tonyo chose that.

196
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:08,300
- Really?
- He's the one who said

197
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:10,333
that I'd give it to you.

198
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:13,167
Too bad, I should have brought
him with me.

199
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:16,200
But he hasn't been discharged
from the hospital yet.

200
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:18,733
Is that it?
Tonyo, your partner,

201
00:10:18,867 --> 00:10:21,400
aren't you two getting along?

202
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:22,400
Oh my...

203
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,767
- Just a little?
- Just a little, yes.

204
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:27,567
Let's see how little it is.

205
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:31,000
- That's a lot!
- Yes.

206
00:10:31,133 --> 00:10:34,067
You know, I think sometimes,

207
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:38,967
maybe it's hard to fit me
into your schedule.

208
00:10:39,133 --> 00:10:42,300
Because you know, your dates,
that's it.

209
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:43,733
No.

210
00:10:43,867 --> 00:10:46,400
Of course, my priority
is still work.

211
00:10:46,533 --> 00:10:47,267
Good.

212
00:10:47,867 --> 00:10:49,200
That's good.

213
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:52,500
Okay, Bobby, I'll be back.

214
00:10:52,633 --> 00:10:53,867
I just have to talk
to someone, okay?

215
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:54,900
- Okay.
- Okay.

216
00:10:56,867 --> 00:10:57,567
Father...

217
00:11:03,667 --> 00:11:04,733
Father?

218
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:07,200
Is what I heard true?

219
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,033
You called me Father?

220
00:11:14,933 --> 00:11:18,933
Does this mean
you accept me already?

221
00:11:19,267 --> 00:11:20,300
Yes, Father.

222
00:11:21,033 --> 00:11:23,533
Sorry, it took a while.

223
00:11:24,533 --> 00:11:27,067
But I'm happy to finally
see you.

224
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:31,967
Because honestly,
when I was a kid,

225
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:34,633
I accepted that I didn't have
a father.

226
00:11:34,767 --> 00:11:36,400
I thought, I'll never...

227
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:38,300
I'll never see you again.

228
00:11:39,567 --> 00:11:41,467
But now that you're here,

229
00:11:41,633 --> 00:11:44,000
it feels like my heart
has been rebuilt...

230
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:52,433
My heart that was missing
something.

231
00:11:54,300 --> 00:11:58,233
Don't worry, Father,
I'll make it up to you.

232
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:04,200
From now on, I'll accept
that I have a father.

233
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,567
Thank you very much, my child.

234
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,567
Bobby,

235
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:25,867
don't worry.

236
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,100
My life will be long.

237
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:34,733
I'll make up for the years that
have passed without a father.

238
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:39,300
Thank you very much.

239
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:45,533
This is the biggest and best
gift I've received in my life.

240
00:12:57,767 --> 00:13:01,667
Hi, hello.

241
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:07,167
I wish you and Faye were
the only children I have.

242
00:13:08,433 --> 00:13:09,300
Wait.

243
00:13:09,567 --> 00:13:13,100
Father, what's with you?
Why do you say that?

244
00:13:13,233 --> 00:13:18,667
Isn't the Vice Mayor the one who
will follow in your footsteps?

245
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:21,733
Don't mind that.

246
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:23,633
I only said that because
Glen and I

247
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:26,533
had a misunderstanding lately.

248
00:13:26,667 --> 00:13:28,567
That's okay, that's okay.

249
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,033
Ma'am Bobby,

250
00:13:31,167 --> 00:13:33,867
Mayor, good evening.
Happy birthday.

251
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,500
- Thank you.
- What are you doing here?

252
00:13:35,633 --> 00:13:37,667
Ma'am, the missing person
you're looking for,

253
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,200
Jun Alferez.

254
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:43,067
His body was found in a banana
plantation near De Los Santos.

255
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,267
Wait, wait.

256
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,433
Do you mean he's dead?

257
00:13:46,667 --> 00:13:47,767
Yes, Mayor.

258
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:49,567
There were gunshot wounds
to the chest,

259
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:52,567
and it looks like he was
tortured before he was buried.

260
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:54,900
If the dog hadn't dug up
the grave he was buried in,

261
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:56,233
he might not have been found.

262
00:13:57,133 --> 00:14:01,567
Father, that's how syndicates
kill, execution style.

263
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:05,300
Is your friend involved
with syndicates?

264
00:14:05,633 --> 00:14:08,033
No, I don't know.

265
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:12,433
But, Bobby, let's talk
about it later, okay?

266
00:14:12,567 --> 00:14:13,800
Don't leave.

267
00:14:14,033 --> 00:14:18,400
I have an announcement
to make later. It's important.

268
00:14:18,533 --> 00:14:19,633
What is it?

269
00:14:19,767 --> 00:14:20,800
Well, later.

270
00:14:20,933 --> 00:14:22,533
- Okay.
- Okay.

271
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:37,033
- Oh, Faye, my child!
- Happy birthday!

272
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:39,433
By the way, you take care
of your sister, huh?

273
00:14:39,567 --> 00:14:40,900
Oh, is she here?

274
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:42,400
Yeah, Bobby is there.

275
00:14:42,533 --> 00:14:44,667
- Okay.
- Bobby!

276
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,233
- Faye!
- Bobby! Thank you.

277
00:14:46,367 --> 00:14:47,967
It's good that you came.

278
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:50,667
Hello.

279
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:52,867
Miss, we'll take these out.

280
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,800
- Sure, Sir.
- Oh, me too.

281
00:14:55,467 --> 00:14:57,367
Add some rice.
We weren't able to cook rice.

282
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:59,400
We weren't able
to cook rice because...

283
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:01,800
What are you looking at, Cheka?

284
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:05,333
Madam, Bobby is here,

285
00:15:05,467 --> 00:15:07,633
and she brought with her
two insects!

286
00:15:07,767 --> 00:15:08,867
There!

287
00:15:10,667 --> 00:15:14,533
My god, that's so cheap
and atrocious!

288
00:15:14,667 --> 00:15:15,600
Right...

289
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:17,267
It's so ugly!

290
00:15:17,533 --> 00:15:20,633
It's embarrassing
to our guests, Madam!

291
00:15:21,567 --> 00:15:22,767
Kick them out!

292
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,433
I got you, Madam.

293
00:15:26,567 --> 00:15:27,533
Watch me.

294
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:33,100
Don't you want us to see this?

295
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:34,167
There.

296
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:35,533
Excuse me!

297
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,133
What are you doing?

298
00:15:38,267 --> 00:15:39,500
Are you allowed to do that?

299
00:15:39,633 --> 00:15:41,800
Abdul, I think she'll be
taking out food too.

300
00:15:41,933 --> 00:15:43,033
Miss, here's the line.

301
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:44,367
Just fall in line.

302
00:15:45,567 --> 00:15:51,033
Your faces are as thick
as your fats.

303
00:15:52,733 --> 00:15:56,167
You should have waited
for the guests to sing

304
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:57,967
Happy Birthday to the Mayor.

305
00:15:58,100 --> 00:16:00,667
And not like you're acting
like ugly,

306
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:05,267
starving people who got ahead
of the guests. Yuck.

307
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:11,600
I can accept
that we're starving.

308
00:16:11,767 --> 00:16:15,833
I can still accept
that we have a lot of fats.

309
00:16:17,233 --> 00:16:20,167
But the ugly thing?

310
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:22,167
You're already offensive.

311
00:16:24,867 --> 00:16:25,767
Oh my god!

312
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,467
Take that back!

313
00:16:29,733 --> 00:16:31,633
No way.

314
00:16:31,767 --> 00:16:33,333
I won't take it back.

315
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:37,633
You're not even embarrassed.

316
00:16:37,767 --> 00:16:38,833
My gosh.

317
00:16:38,967 --> 00:16:41,867
Don't you have any coffee,
and aren't you even nervous?

318
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:43,767
You're still wearing
grass skirts, man.

319
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:46,900
It's driving me crazy!

320
00:16:47,033 --> 00:16:48,067
- Get out!
- Abdul...

321
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,167
Yes?

322
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,467
Hold her.

323
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:53,033
- Sure thing.
- What are you doing? Go away!

324
00:16:54,433 --> 00:16:57,200
- Hey, what are you doing?
- In the name of Shawee...

325
00:16:57,333 --> 00:17:00,800
- Go. Deserve!
- I'll punish you.

326
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:07,200
Protect Cheka, Cheka.

327
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:08,500
That's enough!

328
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:12,967
How are you doing there?

329
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:14,200
Are you okay?

330
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:17,700
I'm afraid because I'll transfer
me to a different prison.

331
00:17:17,867 --> 00:17:19,200
What are you talking
about there?

332
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:20,700
You're not the one
I'm talking to.

333
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,467
Don't feel close.

334
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:23,967
I'm happy, Bok.

335
00:17:24,233 --> 00:17:25,700
I'm very happy.

336
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,700
Your remark is so corny.

337
00:17:28,467 --> 00:17:30,333
What, are you and Enriquez
together?

338
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:32,533
Where did that come from?

339
00:17:32,933 --> 00:17:35,167
I just said that I'm happy.

340
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:40,067
Admit it.
You can't hide anymore.

341
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,767
Okay, let's talk later.

342
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:46,133
Work on that first.

343
00:17:46,267 --> 00:17:48,767
Oh, hey, hey, hey. Okay, okay.

344
00:17:59,133 --> 00:18:00,333
That's enough!

345
00:18:02,233 --> 00:18:03,167
Cheka, come on.

346
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:05,667
- I'm hurt!
- What is that? That's enough!

347
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:08,967
- Ma'am!
-Bobby, it's that woman's fault!

348
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:10,867
We were insulted.

349
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:14,333
She said we're fat, starving,
and not pretty!

350
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:15,567
- That's true!
- No, and she even called

351
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:16,667
for backup!

352
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,033
She thought
we wouldn't fight back.

353
00:18:18,167 --> 00:18:18,867
Yes, that's right.

354
00:18:20,233 --> 00:18:22,067
Abdul, that's enough, okay?

355
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:26,667
Ma'am Sophia, I'm sorry.

356
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,667
Please, Bobby...

357
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:35,067
I can put up with you because
you're Joaquin's daughter,

358
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:37,600
but these guys you're with,

359
00:18:38,667 --> 00:18:40,067
send them away.

360
00:18:43,667 --> 00:18:46,733
Mar, Abdul, come on.

361
00:18:47,867 --> 00:18:50,000
You guys are going to cause
trouble at the Mayor's birthday.

362
00:18:51,267 --> 00:18:53,933
Okay, Bobby, we're leaving.

363
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:58,367
But wait, we still have
something to do...

364
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:02,067
Hey! Madam...

365
00:19:02,967 --> 00:19:05,000
Miss, the takeout!

366
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:06,633
Yes, we asked for that
a while ago.

367
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:09,500
- Oh, hurry up. Maybe the...
- Miss, I said the rice...

368
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:10,867
- It's gone.
- Let's go.

369
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:14,033
- Friend, your dress.
- My dress. Is that it?

370
00:19:14,167 --> 00:19:15,433
Mister, thank you, huh?

371
00:19:15,567 --> 00:19:16,333
- Come on, walk me out.
- Okay, Bobby.

372
00:19:16,467 --> 00:19:18,167
Bobby.

373
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:19,733
Oh, I'm sorry.

374
00:19:19,867 --> 00:19:20,967
Everything will be okay.

375
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:23,533
Everything will be okay.
Please assist them.

376
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:34,933
Get down!

377
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:41,667
That's a gunshot!

378
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:42,700
It's coming from there.

379
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:43,900
Let's go!

380
00:19:45,033 --> 00:19:47,400
One, two, three!

381
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:00,033
Get out!

382
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:02,300
Come on!

383
00:20:05,167 --> 00:20:06,500
Come on, I said!

384
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,033
Dizon!

385
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:16,833
Monty, get out of there!

386
00:20:16,967 --> 00:20:18,100
Hurry!

387
00:21:18,767 --> 00:21:19,433
Hello?

388
00:21:20,567 --> 00:21:23,233
Boss, thank you
for letting me escape.

389
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:24,600
Monty?

390
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:27,300
What happened to you?

391
00:21:27,567 --> 00:21:29,533
Boss, there was an exchange
of gunshots earlier.

392
00:21:29,667 --> 00:21:31,133
<i> Boss, help me.</i>

393
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,133
For sure, the police
are looking for me.

394
00:21:33,267 --> 00:21:35,133
Boss, I don't know where to go.

395
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,733
Okay.

396
00:21:39,233 --> 00:21:40,500
Where are you now?

397
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:42,533
I'll text you an address.

398
00:21:42,867 --> 00:21:44,133
Go there.

399
00:21:44,567 --> 00:21:45,667
I'll take care of you.

400
00:21:45,967 --> 00:21:47,167
Boss, thank you.

401
00:22:01,033 --> 00:22:02,433
Dante.

402
00:22:02,733 --> 00:22:03,900
What happened?

403
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:06,833
There were a lot of them,
but they were all stupid.

404
00:22:08,433 --> 00:22:10,767
It would have been better
if they had killed Monty first.

405
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,833
Then we wouldn't have had
any problems.

406
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:15,567
Boss, sorry, Monty escaped.

407
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:18,933
I know! He just called me!

408
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:22,233
I texted him an address.
Go see him, too.

409
00:22:22,567 --> 00:22:25,833
Don't make the same mistake
of letting Monty escape again.

410
00:22:25,967 --> 00:22:29,267
If those police catch him,
we'll all be dead.

411
00:22:32,867 --> 00:22:33,667
<i> Okay, boss.</i>

412
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:36,000
You're ruining my schedule.

413
00:22:36,433 --> 00:22:37,900
Wait for me to get there, okay?

414
00:22:38,933 --> 00:22:41,233
I'll kill that idiot myself.

415
00:22:41,533 --> 00:22:42,400
Yes, boss.

416
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:00,967
Glen, what are you doing?

417
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:08,600
I hope I'm wrong about you.

418
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:42,400
Is Faye your girlfriend now?

419
00:23:42,667 --> 00:23:43,367
Not yet, right?

420
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,700
May the best man win.

421
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:45,800
Did Daddy tell you already?

422
00:23:45,933 --> 00:23:47,467
- Which one?
- He's planning to announce

423
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,667
at the party later
that you're his daughter.

424
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:50,733
- What?
- Why?

425
00:23:50,867 --> 00:23:52,200
Don't you want to be introduced?

426
00:23:52,333 --> 00:23:53,500
You know that, right?

427
00:23:53,633 --> 00:23:55,233
Ma'am Sophia doesn't like me.

428
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,500
You need to help us.

429
00:23:56,633 --> 00:23:59,900
Didn't Monty mention to you
where he could go or hide?

430
00:24:00,033 --> 00:24:00,900
Nothing, sir.

431
00:24:01,033 --> 00:24:02,667
What are you doing here, Glen?

432
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:03,533
Kneel!

433
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:05,167
Boss, what does this mean?

434
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:06,033
What is this?

435
00:24:06,167 --> 00:24:08,233
Bobby, did you see Daddy?

436
00:24:08,367 --> 00:24:09,400
No, I didn't.
